We were given our appetizers and wine within 10~ minutes but it took about 40+  minutes for the main course to come out. We were skeptical upon seeing this but decided to stick it out. NOT THE SAME AS THE RIVER FRONT LOCATION!!!!!  The place is fancier than the Riverfront location. It seems to strictly to draw the young, trendy crowd that has moved into this area of Biscayne Blvd, just north of downtown and down the street from the Adrienne Arsht center.  The only real redeeming thing about this location is the view and only if you are sitting outside at a table next to the railing. Very nice views.  The food is not terrible and actually rather average but compared to the original location on the river, the food is rather sub par. It does not seem as fresh. The fish is fine but the sides seem to have been sitting under a heat lamp for some time.  As mentioned in several other reviews, the service is lacking but there are a few people that really shine trying to smooth out the issues that occur in the rest of the restaurant experience.  The really sad part about this location is that the river front location has better, fresher food, nicer views, and a much more mixed and relaxed crowd that range from people dressed for a fancy night out to people who have arrived by boat wearing bermuda shorts, flip flops and a t-shirt.  Spend the extra 15 minutes to get to the river front location and really enjoy what Casablanca Seafood is all about.
